"Edit stats & bio" lets them tweak anything before saving

How this maps to your stack:
The "generate" step is where your Spring Boot backend earns its place. Instead of randomising in the browser, you'd call POST /api/characters/generate and the server rolls the stats based on class rules, picks a bio, and returns the full character object. The frontend just receives it and plays the reveal animation.
Once the user hits save after editing, a second call PUT /api/characters/{id} persists their changes to MySQL. That's the full loop вАФ generate on the server, reveal on the frontend, save edits back to the database.оБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: no it's prefilled in already but the user can update the info if they want - write this in a structred way and make it simpleno it's prefilled in already but the user can update the info if they want - write this in a structred way and make it simple10:46оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: Got it вАФ the character info is already filled in when the card reveals.Got it вАФ the character info is already filled in when the card reveals. The user can optionally edit it, then save. Simple flow:оВПClaude's response was interrupted.Try againоБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: make it smplemake it smple10:46оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: Three steps, that's it:VConnecting to visualize...Three steps, that's it:

Generate вАФ Spring Boot creates the character with prefilled stats, name, bio, class and element based on what the user picked
Reveal вАФ the card flips and shows everything already filled in
Edit & save вАФ the user can change any field they want, or just leave it and save as-is

The edit step is completely optional. If they like what was generated, they just hit save and it goes straight to MySQL. Nothing is blank, nothing needs to be typed вАФ the user is just reviewing and optionally tweaking.оБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: what would the project structure look like for sqlwhat would the project structure look like for sql10:47оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: Here's the project structure for your MySQL + Spring Boot setup:Here's the project structure for your MySQL + Spring Boot setup:
characterapp/
вФВ
вФЬвФАвФА src/main/java/com/characterapp/
вФВ   вФВ
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА controller/
вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА CharacterController.java     вЖР handles HTTP requests
вФВ   вФВ
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА service/
вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА CharacterService.java        вЖР generation logic lives here
вФВ   вФВ
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА repository/
вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА CharacterRepository.java     вЖР talks to character table
вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА PlayerRepository.java        вЖР talks to player table
вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА ClassRepository.java         вЖР talks to class table
вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА ElementRepository.java       вЖР talks to element table
вФВ   вФВ
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА model/
вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА Character.java               вЖР maps to characters table
вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА Player.java                  вЖР maps to players table
вФВ   вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА Class.java                   вЖР maps to classes table
вФВ   вФВ   вФФвФАвФА Element.java                 вЖР maps to elements table
вФВ   вФВ
