вФВ
вФЬвФАвФА src/main/resources/
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА application.properties           вЖР MySQL connection config
вФВ   вФФвФАвФА data.sql                         вЖР seed data for class & element tables
вФВ
вФФвФАвФА pom.xml                              вЖР Maven dependencies
The key thing to understand is what each folder does:

model/ вАФ your Java classes that mirror your MySQL tables exactly
repository/ вАФ one file per table, Spring auto-generates the SQL queries
service/ вАФ where the character generation logic runs (rolls stats, picks bio, prefills everything)
controller/ вАФ the endpoints your JS frontend calls (GET, POST, PUT)
data.sql вАФ pre-loads your class and element tables with options like Warrior, Mage, Fire, Water so they're ready on startup

The data.sql file is important for your app because class and element are lookup tables вАФ they never change, so you seed them once:
sqlINSERT INTO class (class_name) VALUES ('Warrior'), ('Mage'), ('Rogue'), ('Ranger');
INSERT INTO element (element_name) VALUES ('Fire'), ('Water'), ('Earth'), ('Wind');
Want me to write out any of these files in full?оБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: the structure for jsthe structure for js10:48оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: That's it вАФ 5 JS files, each with one clear job:characterapp/
