вФВ
вФЬвФАвФА js/
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА app.js                          вЖР entry point, ties everything together
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА characterService.js             вЖР all fetch() calls to Spring Boot
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА generator.js                    вЖР prefills the card with generated data
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА card.js                         вЖР handles card reveal / flip
вФВ   вФФвФАвФА form.js                         вЖР handles edit form & save
вФВ
вФФвФАвФА assets/
    вФФвФАвФА images/                         вЖР any artwork or icons
That's it вАФ 5 JS files, each with one clear job:

app.js вАФ starts the app, listens for button clicks, calls the other files
characterService.js вАФ only file that uses fetch(), talks to your Spring Boot API
generator.js вАФ takes the API response and fills in the card fields
card.js вАФ handles the flip animation and reveal
form.js вАФ manages the edit form, lets user update fields, calls save

How they connect:
app.js
  вЖУ calls
characterService.js  вЖТ  Spring Boot API  вЖТ  MySQL
  вЖУ returns data
generator.js         вЖТ  prefills card fields
  вЖУ
card.js              вЖТ  flips and reveals card
  вЖУ user edits
form.js              вЖТ  saves changes back via characterService.js
Simple rule вАФ only characterService.js ever touches fetch(). Every other file just reads or updates the DOM. Keeps it clean and easy to debug.оБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: when you click generate the character card pops upwhen you click generate the character card pops up10:50оГОоБ§оБЦоАїYou said: please write this in a notes format for me to copyplease write this in a notes format for me to copy10:50оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: Character App вАФ How It WorksCharacter App вАФ How It Works

