Why

If you add the MySQL dependency now and connect to the wrong database you could break things
Once they set up the database they will share the connection details
You just add those details to application.properties and everything connects


What You Can Do Now Without The Database

Write CharacterRepository.java вЬЕ
Write CharacterService.java вЬЕ
Write CharacterController.java вЬЕ
Leave application.properties empty for now


What You Wait For

Their database URL
Username
Password
Database name


Once They Share The Details You Just Add This
propertiesspring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://their-host:3306/dnddb
spring.datasource.username=their-username
spring.datasource.password=their-password
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update

Simple Rule

Write your code now
Connect to the database later
Do not let waiting block your progress
