оБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: do i need to do the DTO for character?do i need to do the DTO for character? bradley did that for stats15:31оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: Yes вАФ you should create a DTO for character to match what Bradley did for stats.Yes вАФ you should create a DTO for character to match what Bradley did for stats.

What is a DTO

DTO = Data Transfer Object
It controls what data gets sent to the frontend
Instead of sending the whole database object you send only what is needed


Bradley created these for stats:
DTOs/stat/CreateStatsRequest.java
DTOs/stat/StatsResponse.java
You need to create these for character:
DTOs/character/CreateCharacterRequest.java
DTOs/character/CharacterResponse.java

CreateCharacterRequest.java
javapackage com.example.Create_Character.DTOs.character;

public class CreateCharacterRequest {

    private Long userId;
    private String name;
    private int age;
    private Long classId;
    private Long elementId;
    private String bio;
    private String artworkUrl;

    // getters and setters
}

CharacterResponse.java
javapackage com.example.Create_Character.DTOs.character;

public class CharacterResponse {

    private Long id;
    private Long userId;
    private String name;
    private int age;
    private Long classId;
    private Long elementId;
    private String bio;
    private String artworkUrl;

    // getters and setters
}

