The Solution вАФ use application.properties but add it to .gitignore

Step 1 вАФ Add to .gitignore
Open .gitignore and add this line:
src/main/resources/application.properties
This means the file exists on everyone's machine but never gets pushed to GitHub.

Step 2 вАФ Create a template file everyone can see
Create a new file called application.properties.example and push that to GitHub:
propertiesspring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/dnddb
spring.datasource.username=YOUR_USERNAME
spring.datasource.password=YOUR_PASSWORD
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true

Step 3 вАФ Each person creates their own application.properties locally

Copy application.properties.example
Rename it to application.properties
Fill in the real database details Edil shares with the team
It never gets pushed to GitHub


The Flow
.gitignore          вЖР blocks application.properties from GitHub
application.properties.example  вЖР template on GitHub, safe to share
application.properties          вЖР real details, local only, never pushed

Tell Edil to:

Set up the database
Share the real details privately with the team (WhatsApp/Slack)
Everyone fills in their own application.properties locally


Simple rule

Never push real passwords to GitHub
Share database details privately
.gitignore protects you
