Option 1 вАФ Local MySQL
Download and install MySQL on your Mac:

Go to mysql.com/downloads
Download MySQL Community Server
Install it
Create a database called dnddb

Then add to your application.properties:
propertiesspring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/dnddb
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=yourpassword
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true

Option 2 вАФ Railway (easier, no install)

Go to railway.app
Sign up with GitHub
Click New Project
Click Add a service
Click Database
Click MySQL
Railway creates a database instantly
Click on the database
Click Connect
Copy the connection details into your application.properties

propertiesspring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://your-railway-host:port/railway
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=railway-password
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true

Railway is the quickest option вАФ no install needed, free tier available, and you can share the details with your team so everyone connects to the same database.

Once connected you can:

Run your Spring Boot app
Test your endpoints
See your tables created automatically
Use Postman to test GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
оБЦоАїоГїоГєоГОYou said: is that different to mysql workbench?is that different to mysql workbench?11:04оГОоБ§оБЦоАїClaude responded: Yes they are different things.Yes they are different things.

MySQL Workbench

A visual tool to see and manage your database
Shows your tables, rows, and data
Lets you run SQL queries
It is just a viewer вАФ it does not host the database
Free to download


MySQL (the actual database)

The database itself that stores the data
Runs on your machine or in the cloud
Workbench connects to it so you can see what is inside


Railway

Hosts your MySQL database in the cloud
No install needed
Your whole team can connect to the same database
Free tier available


How they work together
Railway          вЖР hosts the database in the cloud
    вЖУ
MySQL Workbench  вЖР connects to Railway so you can see the data visually
    вЖУ
Spring Boot      вЖР connects to Railway to save and read data
    вЖУ
Frontend         вЖР calls Spring Boot to get the data

Simple answer

Railway = where the database lives
MySQL Workbench = how you look inside the database
MySQL = the database itself


For your team

Edil sets up Railway
Shares the connection details
Everyone connects their Spring Boot app to Railway
Anyone can use MySQL Workbench to see the data visually
